  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1940 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet shows a framed portrait illustration of the Russian writer Maksim Gorky. He is wearing a shirt, a necktie and a jacket or waistcoat. His face is dominated by an impressive moustache. The name of the film, ‘Maksim Gorki’ (in the Russian original: ‘Максим Горкий’), is written in Serbo-Croatian across the lower part of the picture.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was directed by Самуил Бубрик (Samuil Bubrik) and released in 1940. The drawing is in the style of Socialist Realism – the only style of realistic art permitted in the Soviet Union at that time.</ab>
